  "text": "Since experimental data on the inactivation of EBOV in meat, organs or animal products are completely lacking, only general statements can be made. The results given earlier on the effect of inactivating agents on survival of EBOV in cell-cultured medium, whether or not mixed with serum [CITATION_1] , are considered higher than what could be achieved in meat. Inactivation by chemical agents would only reduce the surface contamination of meat, and may be less effective when the virus is embedded in tissues or organs compared to the virus in cell-culture medium, because organic materials may bind to the inactivating chemical and lower its efficacy.",
